The National Judicial Council (NJC) has warned the public of an online advertisement purporting a massive recruitment process. A statement on Saturday by the Director of Information, Soji Oye advised Nigerians to shun scammers. The spokesman declared that the websites claiming the recruitment were fake. Oye said there are no openings as portrayed, neither is the NJC considering such exercise for the time being. “The general public is hereby advised against downloading any form online or paying anyone for any recruitment.” The statement added that employment into the NJC will be advertised on its official website when they are ready.